The paper discusses the potential use of leeches as blueprints for designing flexible soft robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The study also focuses on the leeches' nervous circuitry and behavioural modes, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the leeches' capabilities for navigating using optical, mechanical, and chemical sensorial inputs, which could be related to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve analyzing video footage of the leeches' movements, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV).
